caption: Ordered from them and got the Pad See Ew. The food smells weird and doesn't taste good. Took one bite and had to throw the rest out. Would not recommend.
The spring rolls are to die for!!!
I love this place
Food was fine. Tofu was super fried unfortunately :/

The food is AMAZING. I have been coming here for years and I travel from far to get my fix The 3 stars are based on my most recent experience. I understand times are hard but I'd like to remind all establishments that your paying customers CHOOSE you. Please treat them kindly over the phone and in person when they pick-up their to go orders. Unfortunately, Friday I had an extremely unpleasant customer service experience. I'd hate to rule out a restaurant because of their poor customer service.
Thai food, mmm, yummy. The staff was very helpful and welcoming. The place has a great atmosphere.
Great food at great prices. Some of the best Thai around town with a nice cozy outdoor seating area.
Thai food and the feeling at this spot is excellent. Certainly a top place in the area. Prices are fair. Menu is like a place in San Francisco I loved.
Always great food and service.
Thai food and the feeling at this place is super good. Definitely one of the best places in the area. The staff was friendly and observant.
Awesome food loved the outdoor dining

This is our go to place when we are in the mood for Thai food.  Good menu.  Food is well prepared.  I have never had a a bad meal or experience there.  If I am in the neighborhood I will drop in for lunch.  The Chicken Larb and Nom Tok are my favorite meals.  I also love the Thai rolls as an appetizer.
Delicious food, polite staff
Some of the best pad Thai and pad see eiw in the city. Highly recommend.
Great chicken pad thai.. Always grab it on Ubereats.
Great authentic thai food. Definitely the place to go if you like spicy! I like the pad see ew. Its really good, some of the best that I have ever had!

Very elegant and welcoming restaurant. They offer large meals and for affordable prices. We liked the food very much and the staff were very friendly and explanatory. Will definitely recommend this spot.
Noodle dish was oily and not very flavorful

Good sized portions. All of the pad thai and curry dishes are well seasoned and the spiciness level is dictated by the customer. Service is quick and water refills are swift. Very good value for this part of town.
Nice patio with excellent Thai food. Would recommend the dumplings to start. I also like the Pad Thai and the Pad See Ew. Service is great.
Fantastic spot to grab food when in a rush. The customer service is speedy, prices are reasonable, great mood. Highly recommended

Great food and great atmosphere. We sat near the bar. The music there was loud, but good, and the crowd seemed very young and lively, which was pretty cool to see. We ordered a bunch of dishes and shared them among 4 people. The garlic noodles were delish and seemed to be a crowd favorite and the Korean pork tacos were fantastic as well. I will definitely be returning to try more!

Was kind of disappointed in our visit to Noodles in the pot. The restaurant is nice enough, art hung throughout the place with lots of space to sit. The food was quite disappointing for both myself and my counterpart, as the portions were very small (we got a bacci pizza slice after, as we weren't full at all) and not what you expected. My noodle dish had barely any noodles in it and was loaded with way too many mushrooms, and my partner's curry was just chicken with a sauce drizzle on it.. not what you'd expect from a curry. On top of it all, the server was kind of rude and didn't seem like she wanted to be there at all.
You definitely will not be disappointed.
I am always very happy with this place every time I stop by. Their lunch specials are a great value for the quality of the food and the service is always super friendly.

Just okay. Certainly not the best Thai food I've ever had, and certainly not the worst either. This spot is BYOB and seems to be quite the spot for togo/take out orders. Parking on street wasn't difficult to come by and costs $2/hour.  In terms of service, no issue getting a seat on an early Friday night dinner. Place did fill up quite quickly after we were seated so it does seem to be a somewhat popular spot. Overall the service I'd say was attentive, no issues getting some one to take our order, get refills on water, grab out bill, etc.  For food, like I said just okay. The tom kha with chicken was decent. The ingredients could've been chopped up a bit more but overall flavors were there. Pad see eiw was okay but I felt like it shined because I was pretty disappointed with my basil leaf chicken. Thai rolls to start were a highlight of the meal as they were delicious but a bit costly for what it is.  Hard to say I'd be back for this one with Paula's kitchen just a few doors down.  'Til next time!
Great food and good sized portions

I don’t understand how this place is not 5 stars. It’s seriously the best Thai food I’ve ever eaten in all of Chicago and NYC. The food never disappoints, it is a tad on the sweet side but I love love love it!! They have crispy fried noodles with their Penang curry that I haven’t been able to get anywhere else. Their staples of pad thai and pad see ew are solid. If I didn’t live so far I’d be eating there every week. Prices are good and the inside is fine, street parking is decent too.
Nice and clean. Large and delicious portions.
Would absolutely recommend trying out this place. Excellent vibes, tasty dishes, awesome service. I recommend this place.

I love this place, it's my favorite Thai Restaurant. The Pah Thai is the best one there is, perfect in every way. The egg rolls are crunchy and delicious too. The staff is attentive and the service overall it's great. Highly recommended!
Yummy yummy for my tummy tummy. Love the food always...

Who is rating this very very subpar place? My Pad Thai was missing ingredients that are fairly standard for this dish. Jalapenos served with Pad Thai? Really? My fresh spring roll was equally subpar and was served with an applesauce like sauce. Chicago, wake up and expect better!
Reasonably priced, delicious Thai! Plus they are BYOB, and have fantastic outdoor seating. Also, the waiters are very attentive.
Very nice.

I believe that I pot is one if the top three hot pot restaurants in IL, which satisfies your different flavor desires for hot pot. Their beef, lamb, and pork are all great; their sources are the best condiments for hot pot. I am sure that I will bring my friends to here again.
Fast good food, have had almost everything here
I've been dining here for almost two decades and it's consistently delicious and low-cost. The weekday lunch menu is incredibly affordable, and the portions are large.
So incredible

I was so excited when I read all the positive reviews, however my order was quite different...maybe it was just timing? Service 4/5 Food 2/5 Ambiance 3/5 Bang for buck 2/5  Ordered for pickup here last week around 3pm. Got pad Thai, crab Rangoon, and a tea. In all honesty I’m really not sure how they have such good ratings. It was some of the worst pad Thai I’ve had in the city for a pretty high price. It looked nothing like the picture and only consisted of the noodles with sauce and tofu. No veggies, peanuts, or garnish?! It was oily and tasteless. I usually love having leftovers, but this one tasted 10x worse the second day. Boba tea and grab Rangoon were fine, nothing special, definitely over priced.  I will never order from or dine here again, and will certainly not recommend to anyone looking for good bites in LP
Food served don't taste right, too sweet. Chicken curry too creamy, too much coconut milk, color o

Me and my families favorite Thai restaurant in Chicago! Everytime we eat or get Thai, it’s from here - we have been going for about 8-10 years now!! I’ve never had better Thai food, try it!! Highly recommend trying either the spring rolls, baby egg rolls, pad woon sen, fried rice, beef and broccoli, coconut chicken curry, pad Thai, chicken satay, cucumber salad, drunken noodles, etc!! Oh and the peanut sauce is amazing too (tastes so good if you put it on their white rice or on the chicken satay)! They also deliver and carry out.

Mmmm the broth was super clear and tasty... definitely one of my top Noodles In the Pot in the Chicago area! I usually can't eat that much but I can have a large bowl here!! The meat is also pretty yummy but not the best meat I have ever had in pho- for me the broth is the highlight of this restaurant.
I Had Thai fried rice and red curry. Both were good but the curry had very little sauce and too many veggies. They were tasty though.

This was one of the best bowls of pho I have had. The meat inside had great texture and flavor. It was actually high quality meat. He broth was delicious.  I also had the chicken wings and avocado smoothie which were very good as well.

Some of the better pho I've had in Chicago. Generous portions and very fair prices. It's a no frills pho place with a Thai/sushi options, too. I first thought maybe it was a jack of all trades, expert of none kind of thing-- but, was pleasantly surprised. Have been there quite a few times.
Delish!!
One of my top places for Thai food. Looking forward to coming back with my coworkers. This place has an awesome feel to it.
Delicious !
Had a very good experience in here with my wife. The food comes quick and the service is just awesome. Prices are convenient.
The customer service is constantly speedy, good ambience, friendly staff. Will come back again when I get in town.
Good and very well priced food. The Crab Rangoon was outstanding!
The food tasted very good, but service was a little slow and I felt a little sick later on in the night.
Delicious spring rolls.

Been coming here since 2003. Prices have gone up, but what hasn't? What hasn't changed is the food. The food is DELICIOUS and hands down my favorite Thai restaurant in the Chicagoland area!  Thai Rice Stick and Lard Na are my go to selections!
Simple and quick. Service needs work.
Excellent portions for the lunch specials. And it's spice perfectly I will definitely go back
Best baby egg rols around. Everything is great here.
LOVE THIS PLACE. The food is done in a very short time, the waiters are extremely nice. The lunch specials have an amazing price to them and it always leaves me satisfied.
Really good food! Lots of options!
Gotta try the Phuket noodles.  They are outstanding and you can rarely find this dish at any restaurant.
Our food was delicious!!
Great good, great prices. Lunch specials 🎩 😁 👕👍Great! 👖
Very bad food. Disappointing.
Loved this place over 15 years
Service was decent. I ordered Pad See Ew and it was fine, not the best I've had.
Yummy pad Thai
Love Noodles in the pot.  Its a small unassuming storefront with some great fresh Thai food and an added plus its byob.
Good food
A great little hole-in-the-wall type spot for some excellent Thai food! I had their rangoons and chicken pad thai. Great food for a reasonable price. Would recommend!

Very good and authentic, and they use quality ingredients, but there was a little room for improvement. For instance, we didn't really enjoy the egg rolls and I feel like my green curry had a stronger flavor of coconut milk than curry. But the other two people at out our table had very tasty noodle dishes, so overall, we were all pleased. Would go again when in the area.
Best Thai place in town. Fast and friendly service and the food is always amazing. Love the outside patio. Also great for ordering out, delivery is always really fast.

I have never in my life experienced such immature and horrible service. My friends and I went on a Saturday night for our friend's birthday when the restaurant was practically empty.  Because we only ordered appetizers the waiter was ripping the napkins and our water cups practically out of our hands and asked when we were going to leave.  I have never experienced a more rude waiter.  We were shocked by how outrageous he was being and when I asked what we had done wrong he was furious we only bought appetizers.  I'm sorry but when your restaurant is EMPTY, you should be happy with any business you receive.  We were a pretty quiet bunch but we couldn't believe ourselves when he was aggressively clearing the table while we were still enjoying our dining.  He even gave a middle finger to me when we asked for the check!! Appalling, absurd, infuriating, terrible.  I wish I could tell the world how terrible this place is.  I called out the waiter, informed him of everything I am typing, and he still was rude.  All other wait staff apologized profusely.  Never EVER spend money here, I hope Karma comes back to bite the inappropriate and rude behavior we experienced!
Love this restaurant. Great Thai food.
Prices on the menu are not accurate.
Delicious! I can't wait to go back. Definitely get the cucumber salad.
Good thai food
The very best Thai noodles in Chicago. Great service and divine iced coffee.

I came here with my roommates. A nice BYOB thai place. The prices were what you expect and the food was great. It wasn't anything special and the tables are tiny, which is why I can't give them 5 stars. Food is great but the atmosphere is lacking.
My goto Thai place in LP/LV. Nice to eat outside on the patio when the weather's nice or they're delivery is usually pretty quick.
Good lunch portions! Spring rolls were ok, but pad Thai with tofu was delicious! Super quick delivery
Love the amount you get when you order here. Normally order pad thai with beef. And they always pack the box FULL! Great portions and great tasting!
My Fav!!! Thai Place!

They have really good food and is located right in the middle of Lincoln Park. I can grab a quick, delicious bite to eat before 3 PM at a discounted price and be right back on my way to class. My favorite dish is the Garlic Chicken Noodles & The Cucumber Salad. 😍

Just okay Thai food. The veggie rolls were wrapped in a paper that was too hard to chew. We also ordered the pot stickers which were pretty good. The cashew chicken was just okay and well and the Thai stick dish as well. Thought I would be more impressed bc of the great reviews but the food was average at best. Probably won’t return.
The Tom Kha and Pad Thai were outstanding, and came out very quickly. The server was very nice and helpful. Great food and great service.
Great authentic food
I’ve been coming here for ~10 Years.  My first pad Thai was here and it set the bar that hasn’t been beaten yet.
This is my go to lunch place because of their awesome lunch specials. Everything on the menu is worth trying, but my personal favorite is the pad woon sen.

The best Thai food in Lincoln Park! You can usually walk in, but make sure to call ahead for large groups. I recommend the baby egg rolls (the sauce is divine) and pad see eiw, but you can't go wrong!
Not that great.

This is only the second Thai restaurant I’ve been to. The food was good as well as the service. I tried the beef fried rice and the Thai iced tea, my dish and beverage were tasty . I didn’t care for their soy sauce , it had a different taste from what I’m accustomed to.
Not really impressed, just a convenient place to eat at that time.
Food was great, but the service really sucked and it was extremely cold inside. My wife and I had to eat with our jackets on smh... 3 stars because of the food.
Great lunch and dinner plates.

Service was good.  Lunch special where you get an entree and appetizer for $7 or $8.  The food was good.  I am giving it four stars because I ordered something medium spicy and it was very spicy, I'm on my third glass of water!  Need milk!  Super quick service
My favorite Thai restaurant in the city. I love the food here. Highly recommend it. The portions are huge at a great price
Yummy
Pad Khee mao was a large portion and pretty tasty. Staff was okay. Can’t remember what I had previous times but the food is always good.
Slow when it comes to pick up but the food is great!
One of my favorite places in Lincoln Park! Super affordable and fast, and the best Thai Iced Tea I've ever had!
I think this is the best in Chicago!

Pretty good Thai food close to the Fullerton stop. Their outdoor seating is a nice touch, and their service is attentive and fast. I really liked the Tofu Pad Thai I had, and the portion sizes were enough for me to eat for lunch the next day!
Great pad see ew and inviting outside seating
one of my fave thai spots in the city
This is simply the best Thai food I've ever had.  I saw a review that said cash only? But in fact they do take credit cards.

Let me begin by saying I'm super picky about Thai restaurants. I've had nasty pad Thai so many times that I barely even order it anymore. I actually didn't even order it from this place, because I was so wary--I ordered the pad woonsen and was wowed, so I asked to try my friend's pad Thai. It was delicious! This has become my favorite Thai restaurant in Chicago. I've been several times since I first tried it, and the food is consistently good. I also love their outdoor seating area. I'm so glad I was open-minded enough to try this place.
They have the best Pad Thai! Love this local Lincoln Park spot.
Fast service, food was great.
The staff is always so nice and the beef pad Thai never disappoints. My favorite Thai place in Chicago.

Service is always great, it's BYOB, outdoor seating is wonderful in good weather.  Most importantly, the food is well seasoned, cooked perfectly, good proportions and perfectly portioned.  And at reasonable prices.
Good affordable BYOB Thai place. They have a nice patio on the side that is quite and off the street and they allow dogs on the patio.
noodles was authentic

First of all the food tasted great, but I got the feeling that it was haunted? When I finished my delicious meal I looked down and saw what looked like an angry face looking back at me. Talk about the heebie-jeebies!

Been coming to Noodles in a Pot since being a student, that's almost 10 years! Service is fast and food is delicious. Can't get enough of the Spring Rolls or Cucumber Salad. Perfect for small groups. Since I don't live in the area I never ordered delivery, so I can't comment on that. I travel out of my way to come eat here with a group of my friends.  When the weather is nice, the patio sitting area is open. They do accept credit/debit cards.
Terrible food and service
Great Thai food! Great service.
Love this place, really good crab Rangoon.
You have to try the crab ragoon!!!!!
Good portion sizes for the price
Best thai on the north side for years
Great food. Lunch specials are a steal. Spring rolls are refreshing. Waitress not too friendly. The food make up for it... 😊
Always delicious!!!

We sat outside which had a cozy feel to it. Service was friendly too as the waiter respected my request to leave out peanuts due to my mild allergy. The portion sizes are huge! I ordered the pad thai and beef. Not only did it taste pretty good but I had enough food to last me for two more meals. Overall I had a good experience and found it to be a good thai place.
Best Thai food in the area and BYOB. Pick up a 6 pack and eat outdoors in the summer
Best Thai in Lincoln Park!
Love this place! They also have outdoor seating, which is perfect for the summer.
Not busy here at all and they have inside and outside seating
Average Thai place.  Would order from here again
Good enough if you live nearby. Crab rangoons are the only thing I would call out as being great.
Great value, love the outdoor seating options. Thought the curry was excellent
Maybe the best thai food I've had in the city--great lunch place
Great Thai place with amazing food.  I mistakenly went to Thai bowl and was extremely disappointed.  Try there coconut chicken curry....getting hungry just thinking about it!
A nice spot for a quick lunch.  Great outdoor patio too.
Decent thai food if you're craving it. Reasonable prices and easy in and out service.

Unfortunately I have to write this review so here I go! I have been eating at noodles in a pot for years since I was a kid, my mom would order from here. We absolutely loved this place however, during our last visit we received terrible and I mean AWFUL service.  Our waitress was very rude and had a very bad attitude. When we finally got to order (btw, I had to turn around to the table behind us where she sat eating and talking to her friend to let her know that we were ready to order) she had the most disgusting look on her face as if we were bothering her or getting on her nerves. She was anything but welcoming. She never asked us if we wanted anything to drink never checked on us to see if we were in need of napkins or straws etc.  The customer service was disgusting and the only reason I gave one star is because I had to. If I could I would give 0 stars. Before leaving I told the waitress that we did not enjoy our stay because the service she gave was terrible and not to my surprise she ignored us and looked away. There was a guy sitting with her who seemed to be in charge, and all he said was, "ohhh, well ok." SERIOUSLY???!!!  Never coming back!!! It's truly unfortunate! There are way better Thai restaurants to go to that will appreciate the money I CHOOSE to spend at their establishment.
Best Thai food ever!!

Recently had my birthday dinner with a couple of friends. I have been here before and enjoyed both visits. The prices are very reasonable for what you get as well as the location of the restaurant. The food is great and the staff is kind. If you want a local restaurant to go to for a bite to eat and feel like you haven't overeaten, I recommend coming here. Don't forget to get their green tea!
Chicken fried rice is 👍👍👍!

If you like Joy's Noodles on Broadway, well you're in for more of the same. Excellent Pad Thai & Crab Rangoon. Small restaurant not great for group, but BYOB is nice. Friendly staff, but not the speediest service I've had in Chicago....
Please fix your online ordering site so that we can order from it. Unable to add modifications like "no onions" to orders.
Delicious Thai food.
Favorite thai place in the city. Panang Curry is my go to.
This place has really good Thai food. Go for the lad nar. It's made with crispy noodles covered in gravy, chicken, and broccoli. The appetizer chicken skewers are really good as well.
Great Thai food, cool little restaurant on Halsted. I would recommend it for anybody. I've been here a few times and everything was delicious. Only thing I didn't like was the drunken noodles
They've improved a lot.  Baby egg roll, Tom Tum soup, Thai fried rice, green curry recommended
Food might as well be made out of crack. So damn good.
This place has a nice "family owned" vibe to it.  They are very friendly and their food is tasty.  The portions are large, so come hungry.

We dined as a large group and the service was prompt and attentive. Food was delicious and came out piping hot - much more quickly than expected. Lots of good menu choices and the patio is unique. I'll definitely be back.

Favorite Thai place in al of Chicago!  The vegetable roll is a must for me to start!  Comes with the most delicious peanut dipping sauce!  Pad Thai is delicious nice, sweet peanut flavor.  The Chicken and Rice (I substitute brocolli for mushrooms) is aweomse, comes with white rice and gravy that even heats up well the next day!  You'll love this place!

Service is great and the food is absoutely delicious. We went with a group of 9 and our service was never questioned. the food was warm and out in a timely manner. the athmosphere is quiet and appropriate for a date night or a quick lunch meeting.
My favorite thai place. Food is really good, especially Pad Thai. Have a nice side patio as well for outdoor seating, Definitely recommend it.
Fantastic Thai especially for the price!
Very friendly attentive staff!  Summer is the best time to dine here, as there is the outside patio that is almost hidden!  I love their spring rolls.
Panang curry ftw!

This place is owned by the same people as Joy's Noodles and Rice. The service is always great here. Last time we were here, a member of our group ordered his dish a certain way. It came out just right. I also really like spicy food.. When I ask them to make it spicy, they actually do. Also, the Spring Rolls are fantastic.

Great Thai BYOB with some garden outdoor seating. Typically we order delivery or take-out from here & it's always pretty solid. It's my favorite Thai place in the city so far.  What to order: Tom Yum Soup, Tom Kha Soup, Pad See Eiw, NP Pad Thai (Pad Thai with glass noodles) & Lychee fruit for dessert
We are from Portland, OR, and used to lots of good Thai food options.  Since moving to Chicago we have struggled to find a new favorite Thai place.  Today we did.  :)

Ok, I must be one of the few people in Chicago who does not like this restaurant. Their mini egg rolls are the best thing on the menu. Forget the wonton soup, the pad thai, lo mein, fried rice or garlic chicken. It's all either tasteless or oversesoned. I've given them several tries but I'm done. Sorry Noondles In The Pot - you've lost me!

Noodles in the pot is Joy's (on broadway) sister restaurant and so good! Love their crab Rangoon, chicken pad Thai, masuman curry and do many other dishes. Very reasonably priced and great quality!  We order delivery from here pretty often and it's pretty speedy.
I had the spicy chili noodles. it was great! The chicken was moist. And the crab rangoon here are the best I've ever had!
The best Pad Sew Beef and Chicken Pad Thai in Lincoln Park! I've been eating here for ten years and the quality is always excellent.
